A solitary figure in a crisp business suit sits at a pristine hotel window at dusk, their reflection ghostly in the glass, gazing out at an anonymous cityscape of glowing skyscrapers. The room is immaculate yet sterile—a perfectly made bed, an open laptop casting cold blue light, an untouched room service tray. Below, warm golden light spills from street-level cafes where silhouettes gather in animated conversation. The figure's posture conveys exhaustion and isolation, one hand pressed against the cool glass as if reaching toward the human warmth below. Muted color palette of blues, grays, and distant warm ambers. Studio Ghibli style with soft, painterly textures, melancholic atmosphere, delicate attention to the contrast between the lonely interior space and the vibrant but unreachable world outside. Rain begins to streak the window, blurring the city lights into impressionistic pools of color.
